%header.center_stage.clearfix
  %h1 News Feed Items
  .context_bar
%article.clearfix.clear
  %p.grid_4 The News Feed Item is a common thing in The City. News Feed Items hold lots of small bits of content, and typically link off to pages.
  %p.grid_4.omega As a result of the prominence of the News Feed Item in The City, there are several typographic styles that apply to it specifically.
  %h4.rule Example of a News Feed Item
  %article.feed_item.clearfix.gutterbottom
    .thumb
      %a{:href => "#"}
        %img{:alt => "50x50_thumb", :src => "http://placehold.it/50x50"}/
    %p.updated_badge Last updated at 9:51am
    %h1.title I'm the title of this news feed item
    .meta
      %a{:href => "#"} Tom Waits
      in
      %a{:href => "#"} Tommy's Neighborhood Group
    .feed_body
      Hey guys. I just wanted to demonstrate some copy in a News Feed Item. It's pretty rad. If I go on for days and days, it won't show here. Just a blurb. That's all. And that's all folks need to see.
    %article.clearfix.response
      .thumb
        %a{:href => "#"}
          %img{:alt => "50x50_thumb", :src => "http://placehold.it/50x50"}/
      .meta
        %a{:href => "#"} Jimbo Sneed
        in
        %a{:href => "#"} Tommy's Neighborhood Group
      .response_body
        This is a simple response body. Your items may have no responses, but that's ok. Just in case.
